#: ../../scala/http/routing-dsl/directives/security-directives/authenticateOAuth2PF.rst:16
msgid ""
"Wraps the inner route with OAuth Bearer Token authentication support "
"using a given ``AuthenticatorPF[T]``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../scala/http/routing-dsl/directives/security-directives/authenticateOAuth2PF.rst:18
msgid ""
"Provides support for extracting the so-called \"*Bearer Token*\" from the"
" :class:`Authorization` HTTP Header, which is used to initiate an OAuth2 "
"authorization."
msgstr ""

#: ../../scala/http/routing-dsl/directives/security-directives/authenticateOAuth2PF.rst:22
msgid ""
"This directive does not implement the complete OAuth2 protocol, but "
"instead enables implementing it, by extracting the needed token from the "
"HTTP headers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../scala/http/routing-dsl/directives/security-directives/authenticateOAuth2PF.rst:25
msgid ""
"Refer to :ref:`-authenticateOAuth2-` for a detailed description of this "
"directive."
msgstr ""

#: ../../scala/http/routing-dsl/directives/security-directives/authenticateOAuth2PF.rst:27
msgid ""
"Its semantics are equivalent to ``authenticateOAuth2PF`` 's, where not "
"handling a case in the Partial Function (PF) leaves the request to be "
"rejected with a :class:`AuthenticationFailedRejection` rejection."
msgstr ""

#: ../../scala/http/routing-dsl/directives/security-directives/authenticateOAuth2PF.rst:30
msgid ""
"Longer-running authentication tasks (like looking up credentials in a "
"database) should use the :ref:`-authenticateOAuth2Async-` variant of this"
" directive which allows it to run without blocking routing layer of Akka "
"HTTP, freeing it for other requests."
msgstr ""

#: ../../scala/http/routing-dsl/directives/security-directives/authenticateOAuth2PF.rst:33
